      <p>My name is Evan Lutz and I am excited that you have taken the time to view my webpage portfolio! I love Math. I enjoy the algorithms and logic of Mathematics, which eventually led me to the world of Computer Programming and Data Science. The intriguing thing about Programming is that it has the far-reaching capabilities to be applied to the real world in ways that Pure Mathematics does not. I began learning to code with HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap through FreeCodeCamp.org in late February of this year and I now know the basics. I am also learning JavaScript as well as Python. I am learning programming quickly with much satisfaction, and I am eager to find a company that will see my potential, strong work ethic and determination to learn more while thoroughly enjoying my job. I graduated in 2018 with a Bachelors in Mathematics (with honors and a GPA of 3.75) and I am working on my MS in Math. I live in McKinney, TX with my family. I am a dedicated husband and father, and I love to spend quality time with my family. Sometimes this includes letting my two-year-old son sit on my lap while I also “teach him coding”, or let my four-year-old play peek-a-boo behind my computer screen while I debug a webpage. I am also a crazy coffee fanatic, and I love to roast my own coffee and do my own pour overs at home. Thanks for taking the time to check out my webpage portfolio and feel free to come back again in couple days; there will most likely be something new as I continue to learn more skills!</p>
      <p>I am presently for hire. Please check out my GitHub to see some of the small projects and algorithms that I have scripted (including some problems that I have tackled form Project Euler). Everything on my page has been scripted organically from scratch, with the exception of the navbar used for this webpage that cam from the bootstrap documentation webpage.</p>
